    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Maori storehouses, typically raised off the ground; used to keep preserved food, seed, mats, weapons, agricultural tools, fishing equipment, or other goods;, Often decorated, the carvings on the storehouses serving as elaborate designs that advertise the village wealth.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
